article.headline: Wichita State 81, UMKC 68
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Sean Ogirri had 14 points and five rebounds to lead undefeated Wichita State to an 81-68 victory over Missouri-Kansas City on Tuesday night. Kyle Wilson also had 14 for the Shockers (8-0), who are off to their best start since the 1981-82 team also started 8-0. Paul Miller and Randy Burns added 11, while Rob Kampman chipped in 10. Quinton Day scored 15 points and dished out 10 assists for the Kangaroos (0-7), despite shooting just 5-of-18 from the field. Carlton Aaron had 18 points and nine rebounds for UMKC, while Mose Howard added 14 points and Tim Blackwell had 12 points. The Shockers shot 60 percent in the first half to take a 39-29 lead at halftime. The Kangaroos shot 38 percent in the half, and only took two free throws. The Shockers opened the second half on an 11-5 run to take a 50-34 lead. Wichita State pushed its lead to 63-43 midway through the second half after a technical foul was assessed to UMKC's bench. The Kangaroos fought back, cutting the lead to 72-59 on a 3-pointer from Day with less than five minutes left. The teams traded baskets for the remainder of the game. The Shockers shot 57 percent (27-of-47) for the game. The Kangaroos, still searching for their first win, shot 48 percent (25-of-52) from the field, but only made it to the free-throw line 11 times. Wichita State was at the free-throw line 24 times. UMKC's Mike English and Brandon Temple did not play. Both were suspended by head coach Rich Zvosec, and neither player traveled to Wichita. English was averaging 15.7 points per game as a starter, while Temple was averaging 9.5 points off the bench.
